HEADWORD: Warling
<hw>War"ling</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One often quarreled
with; -- <?/ word coined, perhaps, to rhyme with
<xex>darling</xex>.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Better be an old man's darling than a young man's
<qex>warling</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Camde<?/.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Warlock</ent>⟦br⟧
